title: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<?> classSet is not expected class
description: Bug 49235 - ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<?> classSet is not expected class in the output.
OB: When running the code, the output is 'MySomeClass'.
EB: I expect the output to be 'MySomeClass'. This behavior is not consistent with the Servlet 3.0 specification. My code works fine on Glassfish 3.0.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 

1. Set up the servlet container environment.
2. Execute the code that utilizes the ServletContainerInitializer onStartup() method.
3. Check the output and observe that it is 'MySomeClass' instead of the expected 'MySomeClass'.
